-- TEXT-Vietnam money market review July 28-Aug 1
-- 
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 04:46AM EDT
-- None



HANOI, Aug 8 (Reuters) - The following is data and excerpts translated from an announcement distributed by Vietnam's central bank. Reuters is not responsible for the content.

Information on the banking activities between July 28-Aug. 1. 1- Deposit and lending rates  1.1. Deposit rates: (percent/year) Dong Non-term &  1-6 months  6-12   12 months   shorter than 1  months or longer   month 0.8-1.0 5.0-6.0 6.0-7.57.5-8.3Dollar   Individuals Organisations 1.0 0.251.2. Lending rates: (percent/year)  a. Dong lending ratesShort-termMedium, long-term State-owned banks: - For production, trading9.0-10.010.5-11.5   - For agricultural7.0-8.010.0-11.0  production, rural areas, exports, small- and  medium-sized firms, supporting industries, businesses using  high technology   Joint-stock banks: - For production, trading9.5-10.011.0-12.0 - For agricultural   8.0 10.0-12.0 production, rural areas, exports, small- and medium-sized firms, supporting industries, businesses using  high technology   b. Dollar lending  -- State-owned banks  3.0-4.55.5-6.5  -- Joint-stock banks  4.5-6.06.0-7.0  2- Interbank market rates: The average rates on dong loans was on a strong downward trend on most terms, except for the nine-month rate that edged up 0.15 percentage point from the week ended July 25. The average overnight rate fell 0.97 percentage point to 2.06 percent/year, those on one-week and two-week terms  declined 0.57 percentage point, and the one-month rate eased 0.25 percentage point. The average rates on overnight dollar loans did not change much, standing at 0.2 percent per annum. The average one-week rate gained 0.04 percentage point and that on two-week term edged up 0.03 percentage point from the week ended July 25. The average one-month rate dipped 0.03 percentage point and the rate on three-month term fell 0.09 percentage point.